"{\"uid\": \"koreabizwire.com-olympic-champions-earnings-spark-debate-on-athlete-compensation-in-south-korea-289271\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"South Korean badminton player An Se-young (C) speaks with reporters at Incheon International Airport, west of Seoul, on Aug. 7, 2024, after returning home with the women's singles gold medal from the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 215, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6, \"end\": 12, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9854918097387588, \"rank\": 0.014721748546102484, \"text\": \"Korean\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 110, \"end\": 115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seoul\", \"score\": 0.9999991550124765, \"rank\": 8.426904597424067e-07, \"text\": \"Seoul\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seoul\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seoul\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(Image courtesy of Yonhap)  SEOUL, Aug. 13 (Korea Bizwire) -An Se-young, the badminton player who secured South Korea's first Olympic gold medal in women's singles in 28 years, earned approximately 900 million won last year in prize money and salary.\", \"from\": 216, \"to\": 466, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 235, \"end\": 241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yonhap_News_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yonhap\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yonhap_News_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yonhap_News_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 260, \"end\": 265, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9999979336815589, \"rank\": 2.0657510629067453e-06, \"text\": \"Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 322, \"end\": 333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.840836521035809e-13, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, this figure pales in comparison to the earnings of top-ranked players in more popular sports, igniting a debate about athlete compensation in the country.\", \"from\": 468, \"to\": 631, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According to the Badminton World Federation (BWF), An won eight World Tour tournaments last season and reached the semifinals of the tour finals, earning $628,020 in prize money.\", \"from\": 633, \"to\": 811, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 650, \"end\": 676, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Badminton_World_Federation\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Badminton World Federation\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Badminton_World_Federation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Badminton_World_Federation\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This placed her second overall, just behind men's singles world No.\", \"from\": 813, \"to\": 880, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"1 Viktor Axelsen of Denmark, who earned $645,095.\", \"from\": 881, \"to\": 930, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 883, \"end\": 897, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viktor_Axelsen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Viktor Axelsen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viktor_Axelsen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Viktor_Axelsen\"}, {\"begin\": 901, \"end\": 908, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\", \"score\": 0.9999971457464005, \"rank\": 2.8417761613714763e-06, \"text\": \"Denmark\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Denmark\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An's base salary from her team, Samsung Life Insurance, is estimated at around 61 million won.\", \"from\": 932, \"to\": 1026, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 964, \"end\": 971, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung\", \"score\": 0.9999990177439307, \"rank\": 9.82256852776635e-07, \"text\": \"Samsung\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung\"}, {\"begin\": 964, \"end\": 986, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung_Life_Insurance\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Samsung Life Insurance\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung_Life_Insurance\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung_Life_Insurance\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is governed by the Korea Badminton Association's regulations, which cap the starting salary for high school graduate players at 50 million won, with annual increases limited to 7% for the first three years.\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1239, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1052, \"end\": 1057, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9999979336815589, \"rank\": 2.0657510629067453e-06, \"text\": \"Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 1058, \"end\": 1067, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Badminton\", \"score\": 0.9999999998640305, \"rank\": 1.3612870461477038e-10, \"text\": \"Badminton\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Badminton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Badminton\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The discrepancy between An's earnings and those of her international competitors is stark.\", \"from\": 1241, \"to\": 1331, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For instance, PV Sindhu of India, ranked 13th in the world, reportedly earned $7.1 million last year from endorsements and sponsorships alone - nearly ten times An's total income, despite Sindhu's BWF tour earnings ranking only 99th at $54,015.\", \"from\": 1333, \"to\": 1577, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1347, \"end\": 1356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/P._V._Sindhu\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"PV Sindhu\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/P._V._Sindhu\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/P._V._Sindhu\"}, {\"begin\": 1360, \"end\": 1365, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9938520697229531, \"rank\": 0.005860040696104423, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}, {\"begin\": 1521, \"end\": 1527, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indus_River\", \"score\": 0.9999999999872671, \"rank\": 1.277970602414019e-11, \"text\": \"Sindhu\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indus_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Indus_River\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Korean Sport & Olympic Committee (Image courtesy of Yonhap)  This disparity is largely due to South Korea's restrictions on individual sponsorships for athletes, a policy absent in many other countries.\", \"from\": 1579, \"to\": 1785, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1635, \"end\": 1641, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yonhap_News_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yonhap\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yonhap_News_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yonhap_News_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 1677, \"end\": 1688, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.840836521035809e-13, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An has publicly called for more flexible regulations, stating in a recent interview, \\\"I wish they would lift restrictions and open things up more.\\\"\", \"from\": 1787, \"to\": 1934, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The badminton community in South Korea has acknowledged An's perspective but notes the challenges faced by less popular sports.\", \"from\": 1936, \"to\": 2063, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1963, \"end\": 1974, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 4.840836521035809e-13, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Korea Badminton Association currently uses sponsorship funds to support the entire national team, not just top performers.\", \"from\": 2065, \"to\": 2191, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2069, \"end\": 2074, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9999979336815589, \"rank\": 2.0657510629067453e-06, \"text\": \"Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 2075, \"end\": 2084, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Badminton\", \"score\": 0.9999999998640305, \"rank\": 1.3612870461477038e-10, \"text\": \"Badminton\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Badminton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Badminton\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are concerns that allowing individual sponsorships could significantly reduce support for less prominent and junior players.\", \"from\": 2193, \"to\": 2323, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In response to the ongoing debate, the Korea Badminton Federation is considering revisions to its salary cap and signing bonus regulations.\", \"from\": 2325, \"to\": 2464, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2364, \"end\": 2369, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9999979336815589, \"rank\": 2.0657510629067453e-06, \"text\": \"Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 2370, \"end\": 2379, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Badminton\", \"score\": 0.9999999998640305, \"rank\": 1.3612870461477038e-10, \"text\": \"Badminton\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Badminton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Badminton\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Proposals include shortening contract periods and increasing maximum allowable salaries and signing bonuses.\", \"from\": 2466, \"to\": 2574, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The federation aims to implement these changes by next year.\", \"from\": 2575, \"to\": 2635, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"M. H. Lee (mhlee@koreabizwire.com)  Your email address will not be published.\", \"from\": 2637, \"to\": 2714, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2643, \"end\": 2646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"score\": 0.7698060364347112, \"rank\": 0.29902791312902843, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Required fields are marked*  Name*  Email*  Website  Comment  You may use theseHTMLtags and attributes:<a href=\\\"\\\" title=\\\"\\\"> <abbr title=\\\"\\\"> <acronym title=\\\"\\\"> <b> <blockquote cite=\\\"\\\"> <cite> <code> <del datetime=\\\"\\\"> <em> <i> <q cite=\\\"\\\"> <strike> <strong>      Currently you have JavaScript disabled.\", \"from\": 2715, \"to\": 3014, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2994, \"end\": 3004, \"title\": \"http://dbped